# .env - checkout-local Compose defaults for the devcontainer
#
# Why this exists:
# - Provides the tracked static defaults for the devcontainer Compose setup.
# - `start.sh` injects the dynamic `CODEGEIST_*` and `COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME` values
#   when it opens the repository root or a managed worktree in VS Code.
# - Each worktree uses the tracked devcontainer files from its own Git state.
#
# Inputs:
# - Existing OPENCODE_DIR_* variables from the calling shell take precedence.
# - HOME provides the fallback base path when no override is set.
#
# Related files:
# - .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml
# - .devcontainer/.local.env
# - ../start.sh
OPENCODE_DIR_CONFIG=${OPENCODE_DIR_CONFIG:-${HOME}/.config/opencode}
OPENCODE_DIR_SHARE=${OPENCODE_DIR_SHARE:-${HOME}/.local/share/opencode}
OPENCODE_DIR_STATE=${OPENCODE_DIR_STATE:-${HOME}/.local/state/opencode}
